<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Chargé</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State.</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Japanese Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-04-25"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                1906</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                            Viscount Siuzo Aoki, who has been appointed by His Majesty the Emperor
                            of Japan to be his ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary near the
                            Government of the United States, has arrived in Washington
                            yesterday.</p>
                        <p>I beg leave to request that you will be so good as to appoint a time when
                            he may call at the Department of State to pay his respects to you and to
                            make arrangements with, you for the presentation of his credentials to
                            the President.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eki Hioki.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>